--------------------------<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     Bugs</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Damage Adder bug still exists.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Perhaps upping the Duration/Frequency of all our songs to 6/6 instead of 5/5 (Like was done for the other chant classes) would fix our problem as well? Not sure why ours was changed to a different Duration/Frequency from the other classes since prior to that change, they were the same.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Misfires of Damage Shouts</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - On occasion if you cast a Damage Shout on a mob from the outer fringes or the range (Which is very small BTW) you will see the spell effect, get a message that it has been cast, but the mob takes no damage. Since the range of the Damage shouts are so small, there is no reason why we would be out of range of a resist message.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Speed Song drops when not in battle</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - This has been reported frequently since patch 1.50 went in. If any member of a Skald's group gets put into combat mode, the song drops for everyone in the group. This happens on a random basis, but pretty frequently. Since this was not mentioned in the patch notes as a change, we are assuming it is a bug and needs to be corrected.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Requests:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Perception, not fact, is causing a great injustice to the Skald class. We have become DAoC's equivalent of an EQ Druid. Everyone knows someone who plays one and how perfect as a class we are, yet cannot back it up with actual and factual data. Well the tally is in and the Skald players are just tired of putting up with it.<br>
Skalds, at release, were one of the stronger classes because of a number of issues within the game itself. Slowly but surely the Skald class has been brought down to it's current level by changes to the game environment itself (resists, armor changes, RAs). Now the Skald performs in the middle of the road as far as RvR goes. We are neither the best RvR class, nor the worst. This is a good thing, but this also leaves us in a bad position. Our class lacks the flavor of most classes and we have become a one trick pony. With our damage output being average, our range on shouts low, and our defenses few we have only our speed to rely on. <br>
<br>
I want to point out that the Skalds at large do not want changes to the Skald class that will make us the Uber class that people like to think we are, instead the loudest voices from the Skald community are asking for on thing:<br>
The Skalds want our class to be what our class is supposed to be, support melee.<br>
<br>
We have at our disposal only the Speed Song/Damage Song/Resist songs to add to our groups. Since Speed is usable only outside combat, we can only use it to get the troops to the fight. The damage song, while nice, has a very limited range which lends a Skald group open to AoE spells because we all have to stay very close together to have the effect of our Damage chant. The resist songs (without spam finally, and thank you) are broken into 6 separate chants, and therefore, don't get used very much.<br>
So these requests are being asked for by the Skald community to make us group friendly and allow us to do our jobs for our realm, and support the group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   1. Song of Rest</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - This song is valuable, and only mildly so, to a solo Skald, and really only at lower level PvE. Something needs to be done about it to make it actually worthwhile to be used as a group friendly spell. Either the effect of the spell needs to be a pulsed heal (like a Paladin's) or it needs to be an out of combat spell with more Health regen per pulse, plus regen of Power and regen of Endurance. The out of combat version will not effect a solo Skald except in less downtime between battles.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   2. Damage Adder</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - This song needs it's range increased to a distance of 1500 minimum. Anything less than that just puts a Skald's entire group at risk. Since we are supposed to be group-friendly, 700 is a mightily group-unfriendly value. The fact that it's strongest value is 7.0 dps per second also needs to be reviewed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   3. Resist songs</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - The current value of the resist songs and the levels they are attained at are not an issue. The fact that they have to be split into 6 different chants is. Combine these into 3 sets of 2 resists at a minimum or preferably 2 sets of 3 as was done for another support melee class.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   4. Rally Chant</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - This is a proposed new chant to be added to our BS spec. This chant will have the effect of Haste on a Skald's party. This would also not help a solo Skald, but would contribute to a Skald's value in a group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   5. Evade II</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Adding more Spec points per level would allow a Skald to raise his Parry defenses but it could also be used in ways that could conceivably cause problems. By giving Skalds Evade II, we could keep the current spec at 1.5 per level and yet get a much needed boost to our defensive ability. Since the typical Skald specs 46 BS, 44 weapon, 17 parry and the variations from that are minimal, Evade II would compliment our lack of speccing choices.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   6. Fury of the Gods Realm ability</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> needs a complete overhaul. The return on investment is just not there. We have to spend 14 to get a skill that for 30 seconds every 30 minutes give us another damage chant. Somehow we think we could have gotten something a little better as our unique realm ability. If we are stuck with Fury of the Gods as our ability then the changes to it need to be as follows: 30 second duration/Double damage of it's current value/15 minute reuse time/10 skill points. Then at least we could see a return on an investment. Otherwise it's time to go back to the drawing board with our RA and come up with one that will compliment, not waste, our unique ability.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    7. Damage adder stacking </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> needs to be reviewed for the Skald class. Our Damage adder (at its current levels) does not need to be cut in half before being added to the stacking effect. All this does is result in a sometime minor, but mostly lower overall effect of a damage chant. We cannot believe the intent of the stacking was to give us the same damage value as before the stacking. If this is the case, then why are we bothering with stacking them in the first place?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   In Closing:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The Skald class is not everything it is made out to be. Because we can run away from a battle does not make us a powerful class. It's time that the issues stated by the Skalds at large are addressed and not passed over because of a false impression that there is nothing wrong with the class.<br>
Many classes need some work, but that does not mean the Skald class should be ignored. With all the changes to the game mechanisms, it is time that adjustments were made to the Skald class so they could benefit their realm in a more proactive way.<br>
<br>
If you want to peruse some of the general thoughts from Skalds, I am including links to 2 threads of interest:<br>
<br>
http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=37334227&amp;replies=109  (Camelot Vault)<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessage?topicID=346.topic (Team Skald)<br>
<br>
