And evade II is not out of line. It is not rocket science to figure out that skalds have the worst global defensive skill set of any class that needs to be in melee range to be effective, and are outclassed by a few purely support classes to boot.<br>
<br>
All pure tanks and hybrids classes that have 2.0 and a shield spec have en enormous advantage (esp, of course, pure tanks with tank hps) : armsmen, paladins, warriors, thanes, heroes. Some have better armors.<br>
<br>
Light tanks have decent evade, 2.0 skill points (-&gt; higher parry skill), much more hps. Mercs have the same armor type, bladesmasters and zerkers a worse armor type admittedly, but they still overall &quot;tank&quot; much better.<br>
<br>
Assassins have an incredible evade skill, often boosted by realm abilites and naturally high dex/quick, that makes them effectively good &quot;tanks&quot; despite their low armor types.<br>
<br>
Friars have a weaker armor types, but spells that can make up partly for this deficiency, buffs, decent evade and a bit of parry.<br>
<br>
Wardens have PBT, the most powerful defensive ability in the game.<br>
<br>
Skalds have minimal evade and parry, low dex/qui and a low hp table. A defensive skill set that is a shame for a &quot;support melee&quot; class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/4/02 5:02:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hehe</span><hr size=1> We have become DAoC's equivalent of an EQ Druid. Everyone knows someone who plays one and how perfect as a class we are, yet cannot back it up with actual and factual data. <br>
