-----<br>
I don't undertand what do you mean, or what design document you are referring to. If they intended the Song of Rest to be a self only power, useful only in solo situations, they wouldn't have bothered to design it as a &quot;song&quot;. They would have made it as a self buff or such.<br>
<br>
From what I can tell from Mythic &quot;litterature&quot; about skalds, they are supposed to be warrior poets, using their songs to bolster their allies into battle -&gt; group friendly. <br>
<br>
Admittedly, the &quot;of rest&quot; part of the song's title hint at a song primarily designed for downtime, and not useful during a battle. <br>
<br>
However, no one at Mythic ever mentioned that it should be designed so only a low level solo skald could ever want to use it. Each quote strongly hints at *group friendly* abilities.<br>
<br>
I am fine if the song can't be used in combat, or with drastic diminishing returns, but it should be inproved so that there is a point to play it between battle in a group situation, at level 50. The &quot;point&quot; could be anything : double or triple the hp regeneration can be one thing. An &quot;out of combat only&quot; endurance regeneration component could be good too (it will only reduce downtime. End regeneration is really overpowered only in combat situation when it allows unlimited sprinting, styling ...).<br>
<br>
It doesn't have to be as uber as the shaman buffs or the paladin song. An out of combat only ability would be perfectly fine. As long as there is a POINT in singing that thing at all in groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/4/02 5:37:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gisborne</span><hr size=1> Don't take offense, but I still you are missing the point, about what skald wants, because of your past experience as an high level minstrel. Some kind of a bias.<br>
<br>
Skalds don't want to be minstrels.<br>
<br>
When the game came out, there seemed to be a definite and distinct repartition of the music classes.<br>
<br>
The minstrel would be the sneaky, witty type, with a bag full of tricks, able to hide, charm and befuddle enemies.<br>
The bard would be the most supportive to his realm mates, with superb crowd control, and various group friendly buffs and healing powers.<br>
Skald would be the fighting type, the warrior poet, with the less &quot;fluff&quot;, less brilliant crowd control, certainly less support, but beeing able to swing a blade efficiently.<br>
<br>
Many players have created skalds with those distinct images and archetypes in mind.<br>
<br>
To put it bluntly, skald melee ability suck. And it sucks bad. Not THAT bad, but, not counting &quot;magical&quot; powers, it is worse than any class whose primary role in battle is to swing a weapon at an enemy.<br>
<br>
We don't want to be minstrels. Cease comparing us to them, and drag us to their same level of melee ability.<br>
<br>
We don't want charm. We don't want a power regeneration song. We do want to have minstrel rest song improved, like ours. We don't want to be able to charm creatures, or be able to stealth. We don't want long range, area of effect crowd control.<br>
<br>
I won't comment your attack on Roseanne's work or objectivity ... <br>
Simply, I do agree that it seems that minstrels are not at this time a &quot;complete&quot;, healthy and fully working class. <br>
They seem to suffer actually from the same identity problem that skalds are facing : the nerf of their stealth abilities and the double edged &quot;gift&quot; of the 5s cast AE mez that they apparently didn't want have somewhat blurred the lines about what a minstrel is supposed to be.<br>
I might  be wrong, but it is my perception of the minstrel's situation, enlighten me if I am wrong, no flame please <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
But as I have said in the past about Thanes or Warriors, we are not here to advocate issues with the Minstrel class.<br>
<br>
Is evade X or song Y out of line ? Are Roseanne's demands exaggerated ? You have your opinion, I have mine, Mythic will judge (or disregard the report entirely because of their chronic lack of resources, as usual). <br>
But the fact is still there : skalds are facing an identity crisis. Maybe you are confortable with the way the class performs because you came to the class with the mindset of a minstrel. The problem is, most of us are more and more restless and unconfortable with the way our role evolves. I spend more time now kicking butts with my champion on the battlegrounds than with my skald. It's a pity if you think about that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uroseannelottsa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/4/02 6:36:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gisborne</span><hr size=1> Gisborne, <br>
<br>
Iam sorry you feel like I am advocating the class far beyond what I should be.  If you are following the threads like the ones I referenced in the report, you will see I am advocating what the Skald community wants, not what I want.<br>
<br>
We are not Minstrels, nor can we be compared to them.  The only thing we have in common with them is the run song and a couple of DDs.  We have things in common with Paladins, Champions, Wardens, and Thanes as well.<br>
<br>
I post what the community asks for. Scarlet (Minstrel TL) does the same.  <br>
<br>
I am a volunteer who gets absolutly zero perks for being a TL except the honor of deflecting flames when I put up a report or when something gets nerfed.<br>
<br>
Not only do I pay for my DAoC accounts, I also pay for this bulletin board system out of my own pocket or when someone places a donation (Thanks Ed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
I do not appreciate the aside about how I conduct myself or about the TL program, because I can tell you, those guys bust their asses for the classes they represent, and though we don't always get along (I mean how can you get along with a Hibby after all?) they are not biased towards their classes.  They take their whole realm into consideration when they work on their reports, and the game as a whole as well.<br>
<br>
We are supposed to support our group.  We currently do that in an extremely limited way.  This report reflects that lack of fulfilling our role.  None of the suggestions would make the Skald class over-powered because it adds to the realm, not to the solo Skald.  If you disagree, then post your reasons, but know that I do not accept 'bad idea because xxx class has it worse' as a valid excuse.  It is just the inverse of the excuse that 'we should have this because xxxx class does'<br>
