<br>
&quot;All pure tanks and hybrids classes that have 2.0 and a shield spec have en enormous advantage (esp, of course, pure tanks with tank hps) : armsmen, paladins, warriors, thanes, heroes. Some have better armors.<br>
<br>
Light tanks have decent evade, 2.0 skill points (-&gt; higher parry skill), much more hps. Mercs have the same armor type, bladesmasters and zerkers a worse armor type admittedly, but they still overall &quot;tank&quot; much better.<br>
<br>
Assassins have an incredible evade skill, often boosted by realm abilites and naturally high dex/quick, that makes them effectively good &quot;tanks&quot; despite their low armor types.<br>
<br>
Friars have a weaker armor types, but spells that can make up partly for this deficiency, buffs, decent evade and a bit of parry.<br>
<br>
Wardens have PBT, the most powerful defensive ability in the game.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Skalds aren't any of those classes either, yet when I use minstrels to point out that skalds don't have the worst defense for a class that relies on melee to kill their targets everyone jumps on my case.<br>
<br>
Comparing the &quot;rest song&quot; of all three speed classes is valid, because they all are essentially the same. They ALL suck. They ALL are only useful for reducing downtime. Bards and minstrels are more of a support class than skalds, and less likely to solo, yet the skald song should be more &quot;support&quot; than theirs? <br>
<br>
The rest song is there to reduce downtime soloing. Why is it a song? Um, cause we sing songs? Why would it be a self-buff (as someone suggested) if we have no other buffs? <br>
<br>
<br>
As for my comments on the roles of TL's, I stand by them. The TL system, in my observation, is all about advocating your class at the expense of overall balance. By not having a Mid TL, Hib TL, Alb TL, and RvR TL Mythic made sure that the reports would be open for one-sided advocacy of individual classes. It's because of this system that we are seeing &quot;inflation&quot; of classes. Previously balanced classes are falling behind even though they haven't been nerfed.<br>
<br>
Now, within that system, I think that Rosey does a very good job. This report, relative to the majority of reports, is reasonable. That doesn't mean it's not open to criticism.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/5/02 4:31:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald report</span><hr size=1> I can't edit my post, but I wanted to add this. My MAIN is a skald. I used to have a 50 minstrel and 44 skald. After selling my account, I now have a 43 skald and a 39 minstrel. So to say that I am biased towards minstrels is inaccurate.<br>
